header.gameNote: C-USA WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINALS AT EL PASO TX

article.description: Brett Benzio had 13 points and 20 rebounds, Danielle Nunn added 19 points and 11 rebounds and Tulane upset No. 22 Houston 70-60 in the Conference USA tournament semifinals.
article.headline: Green Wave upset No. 22 Cougars to reach C-USA finals
article.linkText: Tulane in C-USA finals with upset of Houston
article.story:
EL PASO, Texas --  Brett Benzio had 13 points and 20 rebounds, Danielle Nunn added 19 points and 11 rebounds and Tulane upset No. 22 Houston 70-60 on Friday in the Conference USA tournament semifinals.

Fourth-seeded Tulane (22-9) held off a second-half charge from top-seeded Houston (26-50) by making its free throws in the closing minutes.

Porsche Landry had 18 points and six assists for Houston (27-4), and Lesslee Mason added 16 points and 10 rebounds.

Tulane held Houston's Courtney Taylor to just four points and nine rebounds in the contest. She was coming off a 22-point, 10-rebound game in a quarterfinal victory over UTEP on Thursday.

Tiffany Aidoo scored 13 points for Tulane, which will face second-seeded UCF in the conference finals Saturday.
